nsive values $[a^*,b^*] $ or $\\sigma^*$,\nthat can be compared with the appropriate 'canonical conditioning' based on the\ngenerating function of the local times in the regime of large deviations. This\ngeneral construction is then applied to the simplest case where the\nunconditioned diffusion is the Brownian motion of uniform drift $\\mu$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Aug 2022 07:47:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 20 Apr 2023 11:32:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-04"}
